CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 7, 1956, pg. C4 reads: "Links Have Fun - Pittsburgh Links gave their annual gay New Year's party at the home of Mr. and Mrs. William Lampkin. Pictured, seated front: Mai Ratcliffe, Wilbur Douglass, Lucille Cuthbert and President Lillian W. Brown.  Second row: Gertrude Holmes, Esther Summers, Mary Jane Pago (Page), Billie Butler, Betty Butler, Kathleen Douglass, Rachel Lewis, Miriam Fountain, Jewel Blow, Mabel Bookert and Dr. Rod Brown.  Standing: Gene Lewis, Dr. Charles Bookert, Morris Fountain, Dr. William Cuthbert, Harold Butler, Andrew Summers, Mrs. Lampkin, Dr. Eugene Youngue, Lester Holmes, Dr. C.C. Blow, Elizabeth Youngue and Charles Page. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Links members, front row from left: Mai Ratcliffe, Wilbur Douglass, Lucille Cuthbert, Lillian W. Brown; second row: Gertrude Holmes, Esther Summers, Mary Jane Page, Billie Butler, Betty Butler, Kathleen Douglass, Rachel Lewis, Miriam Sharpe Fountain, Jewel Blow, Mabel Bookert, Dr. Rod Brown; standing: Gene Lewis, Dr. Charles Bookert, Morris Fountain Sr., Dr. William Cuthbert, Harold Butler, Andrew Summers, Daisy Lampkin, Dr. Eugene Youngue, Lester Holmes, Dr. C. C. Blow, Elizabeth Youngue, and Charles Page, gathered for New Years party in Lampkin home
